cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the synthesis of medical images using unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and cycle-consistency losses also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application of medical image synthesis suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
